[p 
	[del 
		[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Mothrayas 
			"Mothrayas
		]a
		": There are a few different ways of defining full completion for a game of this nature. Normally, an endless game of this sort would have completion defined by progressing through the game until the difficulty level is maxed out. However, since this is the version of Donkey Kong with the infamous kill screen, it is not technically endless, and an end-point could instead be defined by going up to the kill screen (and even 
		[a class=intlink href=/Forum/P/445418#445418 
			"a bit further beyond
		]a
		").
		$LF
	]del
]p
[p 
	"However, this movie does neither of the above, only going through each level once in their easiest difficulty - following the site movie rules, this does not constitute clearing the game.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"As such, rejecting - but looking forward to seeing a version that takes on the legendary kill screen.
	[del 
		$LF
	]del
